<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Agassiz in L. Agassiz &amp; Desor" authorityYear="1846" box="[322,432,151,176]" class="Echinoidea" family="Temnopleuridae" genus="Salmacis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[322,432,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">S. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species in the genus in that the spines are banded in red and yellowish to violet or green and have red bases (
<figureCitation box="[576,644,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1942,1964]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Test features and spines of Salmacis bicolor (WUSL/ER/88): A, aboral view; B, oral view; C, lateral view; D, ambital spines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2605946/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). This species is well documented in 
<collectingCountry box="[1064,1177,188,213]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
